com.inrix.sdk

Class RouteManager.TravelTimeOptions

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.inrix.sdk.RouteManager.TravelTimeOptions
  • Enclosing class:
    RouteManager

    public static final class RouteManager.TravelTimeOptions
extends java.lang.Object
    Contains options that specify what travel time information to retrieve.

    Travel times are returned for a specific time and then for subsequent times with a specified time interval. For example, if not departure or arrival time is specified, but there is an interval of 15 minutes and 4 travel times requested, then the travel time for the current time will be returned, as well as travel times for 15 minutes from now, 0 minutes from now, and 45 minutes from now.

    Departure time and arrival time are optional parameters. If neither is specified, then the current time is used.

    See Also:
    RouteManager.requestTravelTimes(TravelTimeOptions, ITravelTimeResponseListener)
